name: 03-Data Profiling and Analysis
content:
Data Profiling and Analysis

Data Profiling:

  • Distribution checks on Amount, City Population.
  • Class balance analysis of Fraud_Label (often imbalanced).
  • Frequency distributions across Job, State, and Gender.

Descriptive Analysis:

  • State-wise Fraud Trends – Identify high-risk states.
  • Job & Sector Breakdown – Fraud likelihood by profession.
  • Yearly Fraud Patterns – Fraud evolution over time.
  • Demographic Analysis – Gender-wise and population density-wise fraud patterns.

Predictive Analysis:

  • Fraud Likelihood Scoring – Probability of fraud for each transaction.
  • Fraud vs. Non-Fraud Profiles – Behavior comparison (e.g., avg. spend).
  • High-Risk Segment Identification – Customers and states most exposed.
  • What-If Simulations – Predict outcomes under different fraud thresholds.
